OL,3,CResidents concerned after future of
OL,4,CJersey Cheshire Home 'in doubt'
OL,6,FHowever, the running costs are rising
OL,7,Fand after income is received from long-
OL,8,Fterm care provision and a funding gap
OL,9,Fof around #500,000, its future is in
OL,10,Fjeopardy.
OL,12,FChairman of Jersey Cheshire Home, Jim
OL,13,FHopley MBE says: "If we have to dip
OL,14,Finto our reserves in a progressive
OL,15,Fmanner over the next few years then
OL,16,Fsooner or later we are going to run
OL,17,Fout of cash. What do we do then, do we
OL,18,Fthrow the residents out? Do we change
OL,19,Fthe model? Do we stop doing what we
OL,20,Fare doing now?
