OL,3,CResidents concerned after future of
OL,4,CJersey Cheshire Home 'in doubt'
OL,6,FThis amendment requests a one-time
OL,7,Fpayment of two hundred thousand pounds
OL,8,Fto address part of the budget
OL,9,Fshortfall. However, even if this
OL,10,Famendment is approved, it will not
OL,11,Fserve as a long-term solution.
OL,13,FFunding discussions between Jersey
OL,14,FCheshire Home and the government have
OL,15,Fbeen ongoing for over ten years, in
OL,16,Fwhich ministers have recognised the
OL,17,Fnecessity of the service but haven't
OL,18,Fdelivered any financial support.
